{{Orphan|date=April 2015}}
'''Joshua J. McElwee''' is an American journalist who is currently the Vatican correspondent for the independent newspaper and web publication ''[[National Catholic Reporter]]''.<ref name="ncronline">{{cite web|url=http://ncronline.org/contact|publisher=ncronline.org|title=Contact National Catholic Reporter &#124; National Catholic Reporter|accessdate=2017-01-29}}</ref> His reporting, feature writing, and analysis have earned many awards from the [[Catholic Press Association]] of the United States and Canada and have been featured in a number of other outlets.<ref name="ncronline2">{{cite web|url=http://ncronline.org/authors/joshua-j-mcelwee|publisher=ncronline.org|title=Joshua J. McElwee &#124; National Catholic Reporter|accessdate=2017-01-29}}</ref>
McElwee was awarded third-place for the Magazine Religion News Report prize of the Religion Newswriters Association in 2013,<ref name="rna">{{cite web|url=http://www.rna.org/?page=2013_contest_archive|publisher=rna.org|title=2013 RNA Contest Winners - Religion News Association & Foundation|accessdate=2017-01-29}}</ref> for which he also was a finalist in 2012.<ref name="ncronline3">{{cite web|url=http://ncronline.org/node/36541|publisher=ncronline.org|title=NCR writers among Religion Newswriters Association honorees &#124; National Catholic Reporter|accessdate=2017-01-29}}</ref> He was also a finalist for the Multiple Media award of that organization in 2014 and its Religion Feature Writer award in 2013.<ref name="rna2">{{cite web|url=http://www.rna.org/?page=ContestFinalists_14|publisher=rna.org|title=Announcing the 2014 RNA Contest Finalists - Religion News Association & Foundation|accessdate=2017-01-29}}</ref>
McElwee has reported widely on the pontificate of [[Pope Francis]], covering the pontiff since his election in March 2013.<ref name="ncronline4">{{cite web|url=http://ncronline.org/news/vatican/cardinals-elect-pope-francis-argentinean-jesuit-jorge-mario-bergoglio|publisher=ncronline.org|title=Cardinals elect Pope Francis, Argentinean Jesuit Jorge Mario Bergoglio &#124; National Catholic Reporter|accessdate=2017-01-29}}</ref><ref name="google">{{cite book|title=Lead with Humility: 12 Leadership Lessons from Pope Francis|author=Krames, J.&nbsp;A.|date=2014|publisher=AMACOM|isbn=9780814449127|url=https://books.google.it/books?id=777GAwAAQBAJ&pg=PA110|page=110|accessdate=2017-01-29}}</ref> He has also focused his reporting on the [[Leadership Conference of Women Religious]],<ref name="ncronline5">{{cite web|url=http://ncronline.org/news/vatican-orders-lcwr-revise-appoints-archbishop-oversee-group|publisher=ncronline.org|title=Vatican orders LCWR to revise, appoints archbishop to oversee group &#124; National Catholic Reporter|accessdate=2017-01-29}}</ref><ref name="google2">{{cite book|title=Conscience and Calling: Ethical Reflections on Catholic Women's Church Vocations|author=Patrick, A.E.|date=2013|publisher=Bloomsbury Publishing|isbn=9781441100597|url=https://books.google.it/books?id=1x5NtXaM3FQC&pg=PA172|page=172|accessdate=2017-01-29}}</ref> the main umbrella organization of US Catholic women religious, and on the tensions between Catholic theologians and bishops in the US.<ref name="ncronline6">{{cite web|url=http://ncronline.org/news/theology/us-bishops-replace-staffer-behind-theological-investigations|publisher=ncronline.org|title=US bishops to replace staffer behind theological investigations &#124; National Catholic Reporter|accessdate=2017-01-29}}</ref><ref name="google3">{{cite book|title=The Catholic Labyrinth: Power, Apathy, and a Passion for Reform in the American Church|author=McDonough, P.|date=2013|publisher=Oxford University Press|isbn=9780199989836|url=https://books.google.it/books?id=mjRpAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA361|page=361|accessdate=2017-01-29}}</ref><ref name="google4">{{cite book|title=Visions of Hope: Emerging Theologians and the Future of the Church|author=Ahern, K.|date=2013|publisher=Orbis Books|isbn=9781626980167|url=https://books.google.it/books?id=LWup8XpC-wAC&pg=PT101|accessdate=2017-01-29}}</ref>
McElwee is also a frequent analyst for US radio and television programs. He has appeared regularly on [[National Public Radio]] programs including ''[[Morning Edition]]'',<ref name="npr">{{cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/2014/09/24/351074916/vatican-arrests-former-archbishop-on-child-abuse-charges|publisher=npr.org|title=Vatican Arrests Former Archbishop On Child Abuse Charges : NPR|accessdate=2017-01-29}}</ref><ref name="npr2">{{cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/2014/10/14/356045096/vatican-report-conciliatory-toward-gays-unmarried-couples|publisher=npr.org|title=Vatican Report Conciliatory Toward Gays, Unmarried Couples : NPR|accessdate=2017-01-29}}</ref> ''[[On Point]]'',<ref name="wbur">{{cite web|url=http://onpoint.wbur.org/2014/10/16/lgbtq-divorcees-catholic-church-change|publisher=onpoint.wbur.org|title=Weighing A Catholic Change For LGBT And Divorcees &#124; On Point|accessdate=2017-01-29}}</ref> and ''[[The Diane Rehm Show]]''.<ref name="thedianerehmshow">{{cite web|url=http://thedianerehmshow.org/shows/2015-02-02/history_of_the_vatican_bank_and_current_efforts_to_reform_it|publisher=thedianerehmshow.org|title=History Of The Vatican Bank And Current Efforts To Reform It - The Diane Rehm Show|accessdate=2017-01-29}}</ref>
He is married to Kate McElwee, the Executive Director of the Women's Ordination Conference. As of 2014 both live in Rome, and both serve on the pastoral council of the Caravita Community.<ref>Caravita Community, [http://caravita.org/pastoral-council/ Pastoral Council], accessed March 2018.</ref>
