The '''Marriage Laws Amendment Bill''' is a [[Bill (law)|Bill]] that was first introduced in the [[Parliament of India|Indian Parliament]] in 2010. It proposes changes to the [[Hindu Marriage Act|Hindu Marriage Act, 1955]] and [[Special Marriage Act, 1954]]. Both acts has a provision for [[divorce]] by mutual consensus of both the parties. The amendment of the marriage laws propose '[[Irreconcilable differences|irretrievable breakdown]]' as an additional ground for seeking divorce. Under this provision any marriage party could file a petition for divorce. It is supposed to make divorce laws women friendly.

