{{Jainism}}
'''Naminatha''' was the twenty-first ''[[tirthankara]]'' of the present half time cycle, [[Avsarpini]]. He was born to the King Vijaya and Queen Vipra of the [[Ikshvaku dynasty]]. King Vijaya was the ruler of [[Mithila (ancient)|Mithila]] at that time.{{sfn|Tukol|1980|p=31}} When Naminatha was in his mother's womb, Mihila was attacked by a group of powerful kings. The aura of Naminatha forced all the kings to surrender to King Vijaya.{{sfn|Jain|2009|p=87-88}} 

== Biography ==
Naminatha was born on the 8th day of Shravan Krishna of the [[lunisolar]] [[Jain calendar]]. He attained [[Kevala Jnana]] under a Bakula tree. He had 17 [[Ganadhara]], Suprabha being the leader.{{sfn|Shah|1987|p=163}} According to Jain tradition, he liberated his soul by destroying all of his [[Karma in Jainism|karma]] and attained [[Moksha (Jainism)|Moksha]] from [[Sammed Shikhar]] nearly 50,000 years before [[Neminatha]].{{sfn|Zimmer|1952|p=226}}

